BVD-CAIRO-QUA-004	Dead Code Detection	Private functions that are never called represent dead code that increases contract size, deployment costs, and maintenance burden. Dead code can also hide security vulnerabilities that might be triggered if the code is accidentally invoked in the future. Identifying and removing unused private functions helps keep contracts lean, secure, and maintainable.	code-quality	low	\N	\N	A04:2021	{"description": "Remove unused private functions to reduce contract size and complexity. If functions are kept for future use, document this decision clearly. Use code coverage tools to identify dead code. Regularly audit contracts to remove deprecated or unused functionality.", "code_example": "// PROBLEMATIC: Unused private function\\n#[generate_trait]\\nimpl InternalImpl of InternalTrait {\\n    fn _validate_signature(self: @ContractState, hash: felt252, signature: Span<felt252>) -> bool {\\n        // Complex signature validation logic that's never called\\n        true\\n    }\\n    \\n    fn _update_balance(ref self: ContractState, account: ContractAddress, amount: u256) {\\n        self.balances.write(account, amount);\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n#[external(v0)]\\nfn deposit(ref self: ContractState, amount: u256) {\\n    // Only calls _update_balance, _validate_signature is dead code\\n    self._update_balance(get_caller_address(), amount);\\n}\\n\\n// BETTER: Remove unused function\\n#[generate_trait]\\nimpl InternalImpl of InternalTrait {\\n    fn _update_balance(ref self: ContractState, account: ContractAddress, amount: u256) {\\n        self.balances.write(account, amount);\\n    }\\n}"}	[]	[{"url": "https://github.com/crytic/caracal", "title": "Caracal - Dead Code"}]	{}	0	{}	\N	{}	2025-12-24 02:01:19.640561+00	2025-12-24 02:14:19.119931+00	t
